ClusterRoles:\
  The following are default with OpenShift\
	admin				-	bind with rolebinding to a project to get an admin for the project (think project manager)\
	basic-user			-	bind with rolebinding to a project to get a basic user for the project\
	edit				- 	bind with rolebinding to a project, can modify most objects in project but not view or modify roles or rolebindings\
	view				-	bind with rolebinding to a project, can view most objects in a project, cannot view or modify roles or rolebindings\
	self-provisioner		-	a set of permissions to allow a user to create thier own project\
	cluster-admin		-	super user, can perform any action in any project, bind with rolebinding to a project to get full conrol over quota/rate limit and every action on every resource in the project\
	cluster-status			-	can get basic cluster status information\
	cluster-reader\
\
	system:deployer\
	system:image-builder\
	system:image-puller\
\
Roles:\
  think rules where each rule is \'91verb + resource\'92 (each resource is related to an apiGroup\
\
\
Bindings:\
  clusterrolebindings			-	exists at cluster level (meaning all projects), not namespaced, can only reference clusterroles,\
  rolebindings				-	exists at project level, can reference clusterroles and roles (create local roles only if a clusterrole does not provide the set of permissions needed for a situation)\
\
\
\
Combinations:\
\
Role + Rolebinding				-	permissions for the subject in the role for a particular namespace\
ClusterRole + Rolebinding			-	permissions for the subject in the clusterrole for a particular namespace\
ClusterRole + ClusterRolebinding		-	permissions for the subject in the clusterrolebinding at the cluster level\
\
\
\
\
