\cf5 Commands\cf2 \
\
What groups does a user belong to\
oc get groups -o json | jq \'91.items[] | select(.users[] | contains(\'93<username>\'94)) | (.metadata.name)\'92\
\
\
What users and groups can do a particular verb on a resource in a project\
oc adm policy who-can <verb> <action>\
e.g. oc adm policy who-can get pods\
\
Try to do an action as a user\
First just as a user 			- oc get pods --as <user> \
Then as a user part of a group	- oc get pods --as <user> --as-group <group>\
\
\
Show all clusterrolebindings in the cluster\
oc describe clusterrolebinding.rbac								(this will show every clusterrolebinding)\
\
Give a regular user a clusterrole (think \'91a role for all projects\'92)\
oc adm policy add-cluster-role-to-user <user>\
\
Show all rolebindings for a project\
oc describe rolebinding [-n <namespace]\
\
Give a regular user a role for a project\
oc adm policy add-role-to-user <user> -n <namespace>\
\
\
\
Show all the clusterrolebindings for a regular user\
You have to run 3 commands\
	oc get groups | grep <user>								(note the group name)\
	oc describe clusterrolebinding | grep -B10 \'91User\\s*<user>\'92\
	oc describe clusterrolebinding | grep -B10 \'91Group\\s*<group>\'92\
\
Show all rolebindings for a project for a regular user\
You have to run 3 commands\
	oc get groups | grep <user>								(note the group name)\
	oc describe rolebinding -n <namespace> | grep -B10 \'91User\\s*<user>\'92\
	oc describe rolebinding -n <namespace> | grep -B10 \'91Group\\s*<group>\'92\
\
